OL,4,Chow many kids does it impact?
OL,6,FGetting rid of the cap is set to cost
OL,7,F#3bn, which is a challenge given the
OL,8,Fgovernment needs to find #30bn in the
OL,9,FBudget to plug the gap in the public
OL,10,Ffinances.
OL,12,FFormer prime minister and chancellor
OL,13,FGordon Brown has been campaigning for
OL,14,Fthe government to scrap the cap by
OL,15,Fhiking taxes on gambling.
OL,17,FHe has proposed funding measures
OL,18,Fincluding an online gambling tax, a
OL,19,Flevy on commercial banks and a change
OL,20,Fto gift aid rules for higher rate
OL,21,Ftaxpayers.
